Intraoperative ultrasonography imaging in spinal surgery (technique and indications). Intraoperative ultrasonography was conducted in 20 patients the technique of intraoperative ultrasonography for use in spinal surgery is described. The authors emphasize that this non-invasive method obtains real time images of considerable diagnostic importance, allowing for a significantly minor use of image intensifier, with a consequent reduction in doses for both the patient and the staff.